        <div class="body">
            <p>You don't need custom error messages!</p>

<p>Use another validator:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$form-&gt;addElement(
    'text',
    'foo',
    array(
        'label' =&gt; 'Foo',
        'validators' =&gt; array(
            array(
                'Digits',
                true,
                array(
                    'messages' =&gt; array(
                        Zend_Validate_Digits::NOT_DIGITS =&gt; 'stupid! only chars!',
                    )
                ),
            ),
            array(
                'StringLength',
                true,
                array(
                    'min' =&gt; 6,
                    'messages' =&gt; array(
                        Zend_Validate_StringLength::TOO_SHORT =&gt; 'You wrote less than 6 chars.',
                    ),
                )
            ),
        ),
    )
);
</code></pre>

<p>Or use regex:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$form-&gt;addElement(
    'text',
    'foo',
    array(
        'label' =&gt; 'Foo',
        'validators' =&gt; array(
            array(
                'Regex',
                true,
                array(
                    'pattern'  =&gt; '/^[0-9]+$/', 
                    'messages' =&gt; array(
                        Zend_Validate_Regex::NOT_MATCH =&gt; 'stupid! only chars!',
                    )
                ),
            ),
            array(
                'StringLength',
                true,
                array(
                    'min' =&gt; 6,
                    'messages' =&gt; array(
                        Zend_Validate_StringLength::TOO_SHORT =&gt; 'You wrote less than 6 chars.',
                    ),
                )
            ),
        ),
    )
);
</code></pre>

